 <text>
  <front>
   <head>THE COURT BALLAD.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">TO One Fair Lady out of Court,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Two Fair Ladies in,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who think the TURK and POPE a Sport,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Wit and Love no Sin,</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Come these soft Lines with nothing Stiff in</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To  and</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">What passes in the Dark Third Row,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And what behind the Scene,</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Coaches and crip'led Chairs I know,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And Garrets hung with Green;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I know the swing of sinful Hack,</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Where many Damsels cry alack.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Then why to Court shou'd I Repair,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Where's such ado with</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To hear each Mortal Stamp and Swear</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And ev'ry Speech with Zouns end,</l>
     <l n="17" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To hear 'em Rail at honest</l>
     <l n="18" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And rashly Blame the Realm of Blunderland</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="19" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Alas like  I cannot Pun,</l>
     <l n="20" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Like  Court the</l>
     <l n="21" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Tell  how Slim she's grown,</l>
     <l n="22" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Like  Run to Sermons,</l>
     <l n="23" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To Court, Ambitious Men may Roam,</l>
     <l n="24" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But I and  stay at Home.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="5" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="25" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">In truth by what I can discern,</l>
     <l n="26" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Of Courtiers 'twixt you Three,</l>
     <l n="27" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Some Wit you have and more may Learn,</l>
     <l n="28" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">From Court than  or</l>
     <l n="29" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Perhaps in time you'll leave High Diet,</l>
     <l n="30" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">To Sup with Us on Mirth and Quiet,</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="6" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="31" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">At  a House full high,</l>
     <l n="32" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">With Door all Painted Green,</l>
     <l n="33" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Where Ribbons Wave upon the Tye,</l>
     <l n="34" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">(A Milliner I mean)</l>
     <l n="35" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">There may you Meet Us Three to Three,</l>
     <l n="36" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For  can well make Two of Me.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="7" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="37" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">But shou'd you catch the Prudish Itch,</l>
     <l n="38" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And each become a Coward,</l>
     <l n="39" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Bring sometimes with you Mistress</l>
     <l n="40" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And sometimes Mistress</l>
     <l n="41" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">For Virgins to keep Chaste must go</l>
     <l n="42" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Abroad with such as are not so.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="8" stanza_type="sestet">
     <l n="43" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And thus Fair Maids my Ballad ends,</l>
     <l n="44" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">God send the King Safe Landing,</l>
     <l n="45" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And make all Honest Ladies Friends,</l>
     <l n="46" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">To Armies that are Standing,</l>
     <l n="47" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Preserve the Limits of these Nations,</l>
     <l n="48" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And take off Ladies Limitations.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
